name: Fe3+-transporting ATPase
classes: Acting on acid anhydrides to catalyse transmembrane movement of substances
reaction: ATP + H2O + Fe3+out = ADP + phosphate + Fe3+in [RN:R00086]
comment: ABC-type (ATP-binding cassette-type) ATPase, characterized by the presence of two similar ATP-binding domains. Does not undergo phosphorylation during the transport process. A bacterial enzyme that imports ferric cations.

references.title: Iron transport systems of Serratia marcescens.
Phylogenetic analyses of the ATP-binding constituents of bacterial extracytoplasmic receptor-dependent ABC-type nutrient uptake permeases.
Molecular phylogeny as a basis for the classification of transport proteins from bacteria, archaea and eukarya.
A Neisseria meningitidis fbpABC mutant is incapable of using nonheme iron for growth.
